## Hints for Future Agents
- The :fast suffix convention on model names is the key mechanism for pricing tiers.
  calculateCostAllRegular strips it, calculateCostAllFast adds it.
- Models without a fast tier (claude-opus-4-1, claude-haiku-3-5) have no :fast entry
  in modelPricing. calculateCostAllFast falls back to their regular pricing for these.
- The "default" pricing entry also has no "default:fast" counterpart.
- printTable now returns []float64 of daily actual costs (in date order) for projections.
- Projections only show in MTD mode (not --days or --all) and require >= 2 days of data.
- formatDollars uses math.Round to avoid floating point truncation issues with cents.
- Table width is now 126 chars (was 103). Cost columns narrowed from %15s to %12s.

## Codebase Discoveries
- The codebase is stdlib-only, single package (main.go + pricing.go).
- DayUsage.Models keys include the :fast suffix from JSONL parsing (processFileForCache
  checks entry.Message.Usage.Speed == "fast").
- CacheWrite and CacheWrite1h are tracked separately for accurate cost calculation
  (different pricing multipliers) but merged into one column for display via sumUsage.
- WebSearchRequests are tracked in Usage and costed at $0.01/request but have no display column.

